@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Cubuc" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any cube appearing on the board, this will rotate
it clockwise by 90 degrees in one of 4 diagonal directions. The
position of the solid colour part of a cube indicates the direction it
is pointing, either in upper right, lower right, lower left or upper
left, so you have to rotate cubes so they are lined up and pointing in
the same direction.

  If 4 cubes or more are aligned in the same direction they will be
removed from the game board and you will get points according to their
number. You get more points if the cubes are all of the same colour;
an alignment of 4 cubes of different colours will give you 1 point,
but an alignment of the same number of cubes all of the same colour
will give you 50 points... as shown on the following table:

            Different colours    Same colour
  4 cubes         1 point         50 points
  5 cubes         4 points       100 points
  6 cubes         9 points       200 points
  7 cubes        16 points       400 points

  If you rotate a cube and it doesn't complete an alignment of 4 cubes
or more, a new cube will appear somewhere on the game board. Just do
not let the board fill up completely because this would end the game.

  As cubes appear randomly on the game board, one of them may complete
an alignment of 4 or more cubes, when that happens, that alignment
will be removed and the game will give you 1 point.

  If you clear the game board, that is, there are no remaining cubes,
the game will end and your score will be doubled.

  Have fun!

@endnode

